1
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:24,280
"Hail Mary, full of grace
the Lord is with thee."

2
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:27,280
"Blessed art thou among women"

3
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:30,960
"and blessed is the fruit of thy womb Jesus"

4
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:36,880
"Holy Mary
Mother of God, pray for us sinners"

5
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,600
"Now and at the hour of our death."

6
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,520
"Amen."

7
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,600
No, no.

8
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,840
No, no!

9
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,480
No, no, no!

10
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,600
No!

11
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,800
"Help!"

12
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,240
Help!

13
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,120
Help!

14
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,520
No, no, no!

15
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,480
Help!

16
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,000
Please...

17
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,280
help.

18
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,720
"No!"

19
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,480
"Help! Help!"

20
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,320
I'm sorry, but how much
longer will this take?

21
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:19,040
I've got to take my vows tonight
and I really can't be late.

22
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,520
- Do you speak English?
- Sorry for the wait.

23
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,800
It's extra work now
when someone arrives

24
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,280
without a return ticket.

25
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,640
Parli italiano?

26
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,760
I ask if you're learning Italian.

27
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:36,360
Oh, I'm trying, but it's
a lot harder than I thought.

28
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,800
Mm.

29
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,640
So this convent
they bought you the ticket?

30
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,480
Mm-hmm.

31
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,240
You're very young
to be a nun, aren't you?

32
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,400
What a waste.

33
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,520
Look at her.

34
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,640
It's a different life, yeah?

35
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,160
It must have been
a hard decision.

36
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:05,280
I don't think of it like that
as a decision.

37
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,880
Very well.

38
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,440
I hope you find what you're
looking for, Sister Cecilia.

39
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,560
Sister Cecilia
Apologies.

40
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,760
- I'm Deacon Enzo, come with me.
- Thank you.

41
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:11,680
- "How much longer?"
- We're almost there.

42
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,760
Right this way, Sister Cecilia.

43
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,880
Sister Cecilia!

44
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,120
Reverend Mother.

45
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:16,520
Your eyes radiate
the light of the Holy Spirit.

46
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:20,080
Like the angels delivered you
straight from the heavens.

47
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:22,880
We've been eagerly awaiting
your arrival, my dear.

48
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,120
I'm sorry.

49
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,520
She says you're pretty.

50
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,680
Grazie
I'm Sister Cecilia.

51
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,600
Isabelle.

52
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:37,400
Isabelle, will you please show Cecilia
to her room?

53
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,360
I have to help our sisters get ready
for tonight's celebration.

54
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,680
Mind your place and do as I ask!

55
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,720
Let me show you
to your room.

56
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:53,000
Our Lady of Sorrows was founded in 1632
as a refuge for elder sisters

57
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,000
before their transition to heaven.

58
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,720
- It's really beautiful.
- Yes, it is.

59
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,160
- Buongiorno, sorelle.
- Buongiorno.

60
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,120
And we work hard
to keep it that way.

61
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,880
Our sister's final
days should be

62
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,560
a pleasing environment
to help distract from all

63
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,080
the sickness and suffering.

64
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:09,640
All of this, it was built on
the catacomb of St. Stephen.

65
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,160
Catacombs?

66
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,720
It's off limits.

67
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,120
Hello, Sisters.

68
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:18,040
- This is our new novice, Sister Cecilia.
- Ciao.

69
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:20,920
The one in the wheelchair
her tumor has metastasized.

70
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,400
So we expect her to meet God
by the end of the week.

71
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,160
You talk about it so casually.

72
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,000
Death is a part
of everyday life here.

73
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,800
Have you seen my daddy?

74
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:35,640
Yes, let's go find him, shall we?

75
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:38,960
It's best to just play along
with their delusions

76
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,360
unless they get violent.

77
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,520
Be careful of this one
She bites.

78
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,880
I'm sorry.

79
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:09,680
Living quarters for the caretakers
are down there and upstairs.

80
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,840
Morning prayer begins at 5:00 a.m.
communal meal is after.

81
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:16,320
And if you have any dietary restrictions
we cannot accommodate them.

82
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:19,720
And this room is yours.

83
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,960
Thank you, Sister.

84
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,440
I feel honored
to serve alongside you.

85
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,680
- You're very sweet.
- Thank you.

86
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,320
I don't mean that
as a compliment.

87
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:38,400
I'm sure this must feel very romantic
but this is our life.

88
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,760
And I promise you, work is hard
physically and emotionally.

89
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,880
So if you're here to find yourself
there are easier ways.

90
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,320
I'm not.

91
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:52,120
Tonight, you do not
have to take your vows.

92
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:55,160
You can still go back
and God will forgive you.

93
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,320
I think he has
sufficiently prepared me.

94
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:08,560
The ceremony will start
at 1700 in the chapel.

95
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,640
Don't be late.

96
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,360
- Oh, ciao.
- Ciao.

97
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,320
- I'm sorry.
- No, it's fine.

98
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,160
I'm Cecilia.

99
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,160
Oh, I'm Guendalina
You can call me Gwen.

100
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,600
My room is there.

101
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,040
Where in the States
are you from?

102
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:33,080
- Just outside of Detroit, Michigan.
- Mm-hmm.

103
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,960
- Are you from around here or...
- Closer to Milan.

104
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,720
You're far from home.

105
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,080
Yeah, my parish closed.

106
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:44,200
Did the priest get in trouble?

107
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:47,600
No, no, no, no, no, no, no
nothing, nothing like that.

108
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:50,040
Just low attendance.

109
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,960
And that church was
my family, my home.

110
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,840
Leaving, I felt pretty lost.

111
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:57,760
But then Father Tedeschi
he reached out to me.

112
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,720
Yeah
He has a talent.

113
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,840
Sniffing out broken birds.

114
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,960
Oh, I didn't want
to offend you.

115
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:17,800
I think that maybe we are all
head cases or runaways.

116
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,280
Which one are you?

117
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,800
Both.

118
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,720
Next time if you want
you can lock the door.

119
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,880
Thanks.

120
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,760
Sister Cecilia.

121
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:54,760
Father Tedeschi, it's nice
to meet you in person.

122
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:57,240
We all feel so blessed
to have you here.

123
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,400
How's the Italian coming along?

124
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:02,800
Così così.

125
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,800
It's fine
I will translate for you.

126
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:17,520
In the name of the Father, the Son
and the Holy Spirit.

127
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,360
Amen.

128
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:38,680
Let us rejoice, for the marriage
of the Lamb has come

129
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:42,360
and his brides have
made themselves ready.

130
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,600
Sorella Cecilia.

131
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,040
Sister Cecilia.

132
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:02,440
Do you promise to follow Christ
more closely by living a life devoid

133
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,200
of material possessions?

134
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,360
Do you promise to free
yourself from the demands

135
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:10,800
of a human relationship
and follow with joy

136
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,560
when he shall come again...

137
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:17,360
A vow of poverty
chastity, and obedience?

138
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,160
I do.

139
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:30,080
May God give you the
strength to fulfill your vows

140
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,200
faithfully and joyfully.

141
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:36,640
May you shine his light
for the world to see.

142
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:46,280
- "How are you feeling?"
- Full.

143
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,960
Yeah, we don't...
We don't really have anything

144
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,400
like this back home.

145
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,920
Cecilia, this is your home.

146
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,800
I know, I know.

147
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,720
I felt the same way
when I started here.

148
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,120
I didn't grow up
wanting to be a priest.

149
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:07,480
My first career was
in sciences, biology.

150
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,880
I was almost two decades in
and I couldn't

151
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,360
understand the world any better than
back when I was in Sunday school.

152
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,680
And then God showed me a path.

153
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,360
He brought me here.

154
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:22,400
This is where I was meant to be.

155
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,720
I'm sorry
I'm so sorry.

156
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,840
Two glasses in and I can't
stop talking about myself.

157
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,080
- I'm so sorry.
- No, it's OK.

158
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,160
- It's OK.
- What about you?

159
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,200
I imagine it was
a difficult decision.

160
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:42,640
I mean, yes
it seemed so far away.

161
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:46,240
But the opportunities back in the States...

162
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,120
I didn't feel like
that's what God saved me for.

163
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,240
- If it's too personal...
- No.

164
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,680
When I was 12 years old
there was this part

165
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,240
of the Saginaw River
that would always freeze over.

166
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:06,800
And no matter how cold it was
I would always walk out onto the ice.

167
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:08,880
And I would do this thing
where I took my gloves off

168
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,000
and I would place my hands
right on the ice, and...

169
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,280
And I would hold them there
until I couldn't feel anything.

170
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,080
I don't remember
the ice breaking.

171
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:22,640
I just, I remember
this sharp pain of cold.

172
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,800
The paramedics
they tried to revive me

173
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,960
but my heart stopped
for almost seven minutes.

174
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,440
That sounds terrifying.

175
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:36,360
I know God saved me
for a reason, but...

176
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,200
I guess I'm still searching
for what that reason is.

177
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:47,560
Now will you...
Will you excuse me, please?

178
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,760
Ciao?

179
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,440
Are you OK?

180
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,440
I'll go get some help.

181
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,000
Cecilia.

182
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,880
Reverend Mother, I'm so sorry.

183
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,800
- I heard her crying and...
- It's OK.

184
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,840
Sometimes we get caught up in emotion.

185
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,680
You have a question.

186
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,320
All right.

187
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,680
What is this place?

188
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:11,640
Saint Helena, Mother of Constantine...

189
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,000
brought this back from Jerusalem.

190
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,280
Here.

191
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,560
He suffered on the cross.

192
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,880
Suffered?
This is the...

193
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,120
Yes.

194
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:43,480
For you, for us, for our sins
For our salvation.

195
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,840
We suffer.

196
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:48,600
In the name of His love.

197
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,000
It is a gift.

198
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,720
Suffering is love.

199
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:00,400
Are you alright, Sister?

200
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:16,880
In the name of the Father
and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

201
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:18,480
Amen.

202
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,400
Bless me, Father
for I have sinned.

203
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,200
It's been three days
since my last confession.

204
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,520
I was...

205
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,040
I was careless last night.

206
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:38,720
I must have drank too much
wine and embarrassed myself

207
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,400
in front of Mother Superior.

208
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:51,160
I promise to carry myself with
grace because I want nothing

209
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,640
more than to belong here.

210
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,000
I'm afraid I've already
messed things up.

211
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:04,080
I'm sorry for these...

212
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,360
Yearnments.

213
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:26,200
Hello?

214
00:23:57,440 --> 00:24:01,000
Good morning, Sisters
Today a new life begins.

215
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,400
But this new year will not be easy.

216
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,920
You will question your purpose.

217
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:09,360
You will question me
and why you have come here.

218
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,680
And some of you will not have
the spiritual fortitude for this life.

219
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:16,960
What did she say?

220
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:19,040
God is good
God is great.

221
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:22,360
- God, my head hurts.
- Too much blood of Christ?

222
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,520
Do you find this amusing, Sister Guendalina?

223
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,640
No, forgive me.

224
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,800
This side of the room is with me.

225
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:36,000
The other, will serve with Sister Isabelle.

226
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,080
No.

227
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,000
Shit.

228
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,480
What a blessing
to mentor you both.

229
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:44,160
Finish eating
We have work to do.

230
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,440
Looks like her vibrator ran out of battery.

231
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,200
What does that mean?

232
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,920
Oh, nothing
I really like her.

233
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,440
I'm super excited.

234
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,920
"Clean their back thoroughly."

235
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,920
And if the consistency
of their feces seems off

236
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:58,520
you let Dr. Gallo know.

237
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,240
- Ciao.
- Ciao.

238
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:06,680
We want to hang the larger
items towards the front

239
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:09,120
and the shorter items
towards the back.

240
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,760
That way, the wind can
blow underneath it.

241
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:16,760
First you have to make sure
your knife is nice and sharp.

242
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:19,040
Otherwise you run
the risk of making a big mess.

243
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,160
I'm sorry, I can't.

244
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:10,320
"In the name of the Father and
the Son and the Holy Spirit."

245
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,600
"Amen."

246
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,720
Blessed.

247
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:54,200
Saint.

248
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,920
All of us adore you.

249
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:03,760
Sister, let's...
Let's get you to bed.

250
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:22,280
Blessed Saint Cecilia.

251
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,280
Good night, Sister.

252
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:56,120
"It could have been worse."

253
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,800
"She could have
given you bangs."

254
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,600
Gwen, I'm not joking.

255
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,960
She had scars
on the bottom of her feet.

256
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:07,360
It's not what you thought
it would be, huh, this place?

257
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:10,280
No, it's definitely different.

258
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:13,000
It's better than where
I came from, though.

259
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:15,640
What do you mean?

260
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:19,680
There is a boy
There was a boy, I mean.

261
